1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 25]

31
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:36,900
If I bump into him again,

32
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,460
could you keep playing along?

33
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,770
No way. Count me out.

34
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,260
I've got standards.

35
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,410
I'm only using you as a cover.

36
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,930
It's not like we're actually together.

37
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,850
I won't fake a relationship
at the cost of my reputation.

38
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:54,770
Besides,

39
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:58,740
playing your fiancé is seriously risky.

40
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,490
You said it like it was no big deal,

41
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:02,900
and I almost died.

42
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,500
Zhiqiu, please help me.

43
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,410
So what's in it for me?

44
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,660
What do you want?

45
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:32,290
Next month,

46
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:33,500
change the packaging of Hugu Pill.

47
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:34,170
Okay.

48
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:37,780
You'll be
in charge of Xia Yuan's election

49
00:02:38,430 --> 00:02:39,660
as guild president.

50
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:40,450
No problem.

51
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:43,980
Also,

52
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:46,820
show a little more respect.

53
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,890
Stop flipping out over everything.

54
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:49,060
After all, I'm the boss.

55
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:51,980
Okay, boss.

56
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,380
I'll try not to lose it again.

57
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:56,610
Alright.

58
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:58,260
That's it.

59
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,570
Really?

60
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,170
Thank you, Zhiqiu.

61
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:16,340
Wait, you're kind of off today.

62
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:21,980
You're one to talk.

63
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:47,730
You're back.

64
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:50,570
I was wondering
why the door was left open.

65
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:51,610
Why are you here?

66
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:52,780
Been waiting on you.

67
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:54,730
How was your day?

68
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,260
Well. It was good.

69
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,260
Guess who I saw?

70
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,060
Who?

71
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,130
Xia Chu.

72
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,290
Didn't he go to France?

73
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,290
He's back.

74
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:19,020
And he showed up...

75
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,020
with his girlfriend.

76
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:25,050
He has a girlfriend?

77
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,730
They're a good match,

78
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:32,930
and they seem happy.

79
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:36,580
Maybe this is how it was meant to end.

80
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,220
Alright.

81
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:40,580
What about Wen Zhiqiu?

82
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,250
I met him too.

83
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,900
Did he tell you?

84
00:04:49,390 --> 00:04:50,700
He told you too?

85
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,460
Of course, I had to know.

86
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:55,540
Yes.

87
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:56,900
How did you respond?

88
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:58,490
Nothing special.

89
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,660
I think his idea is very good.

90
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:03,580
And then?

91
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,250
Elaborate further.

92
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,490
Then...

93
00:05:09,830 --> 00:05:11,170
I'll work harder.

94
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:15,810
What exactly

95
00:05:16,630 --> 00:05:17,900
did Wen Zhiqiu tell you?

96
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:21,050
The prospects of Wen's Pharmacy.

97
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,540
And then? That's it?

98
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:24,980
What else could there be?

99
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:29,610
Guess this is the best I could hope for.

100
00:05:30,510 --> 00:05:32,540
I feel so fortunate

101
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,340
to have you as a friend,

102
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,050
to be building my own career,

103
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:38,220
and to work with Wen Zhiqiu.

104
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:46,800
[Blue Stone Apartment]

105
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,900
Sir, we're here.

106
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:00,410
Here, thank you.

107
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,490
Thank you, sir.

108
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:07,100
Wen Zhiqiu.

109
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:10,810
Why are you here?

110
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,460
Thought you could use some comfort.

111
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,050
You should...

112
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:22,980
congratulate me.

113
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,780
Be careful.

114
00:06:25,430 --> 00:06:28,340
I'm Chu Shaohua's fiancé.

115
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,220
Shaohua told me everything.

116
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,900
Xia Chu is back.

117
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,170
You didn't confess to her.

118
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,780
After everything you did,

119
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,980
why not fight for what you want?

120
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:49,490
You know what she's like.

121
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:52,100
She has always been...

122
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,170
so composed,

123
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:56,900
clear-minded...

124
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:58,980
and...

125
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:01,780
razor-sharp.

126
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,020
Yes.

127
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:04,250
Like a blade.

128
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,290
A blade of ice.

129
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,660
But today, the frost in her eyes
began to melt.

130
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:15,660
And the heat she'd buried
for so long started to rise.

131
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,900
I always thought

132
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,610
we were two souls in love,

133
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,850
growing side by side.

134
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,250
I thought I knew her.

135
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,780
But that's not what she needed.

136
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,250
What she needed...

137
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,250
was to feel the spark again.

138
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:42,930
So, are you going to light it,

139
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:45,290
or back down when things get hard?

140
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:51,220
I'm going to find the fire.

141
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,410
Right?

142
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:53,580
Love never plays

143
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,780
by the rules.

144
00:07:56,270 --> 00:07:57,250
Hold this for me.

145
00:07:58,190 --> 00:08:00,580
You're the expert in love, aren't you?

146
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,220
Alright, stop making fun of me.

147
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:04,490
Where are they?

148
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:08,700
Check these out.

149
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,610
I carved them myself.

150
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:12,540
That is

151
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,020
Chichun Apothecary.

152
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:16,660
[Chichun Apothecary]
[Wen and Chu's Residence]

153
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,290
This one,

154
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,700
and our...

155
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:22,020
Shaohua told me very seriously

156
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,810
that you're a good partner to her.

157
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,250
I'm going up.

158
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,530
Do you get what I meant?

159
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,250
You mean more than you realize.

160
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:05,680
[Chichun Apothecary]
[Wen and Chu's Residence]

161
00:09:05,830 --> 00:09:10,950
♪Strayed from the path,
ask who turns away♪

162
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:16,670
♪Keep silent to try to forget,
yet it clings to memory♪

163
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:23,230
♪Even good medicine can't heal the soul♪

164
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:32,190
♪The machinations of my conscience
drive me into perdition♪

165
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:38,560
♪Let my breath run ragged, run ragged♪

166
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:44,550
♪Lost in love,
how could I ever fool myself again?♪

167
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:45,180
Shaohua,

168
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,490
let's take Xuan to France!

169
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:50,650
You both

170
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:52,850
deserve a broader world.

171
00:09:52,850 --> 00:09:55,000
♪When walking towards the same thorns♪

172
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,610
Three days later,
let's meet at the crossroads.

173
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,700
Wait for me.

174
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:00,060
I'll wait for you.

175
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:03,160
♪Like a fish stranded on land,
you stay silent♪

176
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:09,120
♪For you, I dive deep beneath the sea♪

177
00:10:09,660 --> 00:10:15,320
♪If I had once surrendered to destiny♪

178
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:21,320
♪Then meeting you
was always meant to be♪

179
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:27,480
♪How can I leave you?♪

180
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:33,600
♪A lifelong riddle with no answers♪

181
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,320
[Wen and Chu's Residence]

182
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:39,880
♪Today I see through
fate's cunning trick♪

183
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:47,440
♪Yet I decree your presence
written in my stars♪

184
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:52,400
[Wen's Pharmacy]

185
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:54,900
Good morning.

186
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:58,340
Good morning,

187
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:00,580
my dear fiancée.

188
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:02,700
Let's be clear.

189
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,660
I'm only your fiancée

190
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:06,660
on rare occasions.

191
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:08,580
Any chance we can make it more regular?

192
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:09,820
No.

193
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,020
Why?

194
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:13,460
I'm afraid
it might harm your reputation.

195
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:17,500
Now I don't even care about my life,

196
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,700
so reputation? Please.

197
00:11:19,260 --> 00:11:20,580
Dying's no big deal,

198
00:11:20,740 --> 00:11:21,980
but losing face is catastrophic.

199
00:11:23,540 --> 00:11:25,300
So now you understand that.

200
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:27,180
I'm being serious.

201
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:28,460
We need to talk
about something important.

202
00:11:31,660 --> 00:11:34,180
Among the members of the TCM Guild,

203
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:36,820
Mr. Tian still holds

204
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,540
the highest approval rating,

205
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:39,300
at 30%,

206
00:11:39,860 --> 00:11:41,940
while Mr. Xia trails behind
with just 20% support.

207
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:44,180
What about the other 50%?

208
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:48,740
Wen's Pharmacy.

209
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:51,620
Mr. Xia.

210
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:55,580
I'll discuss this with Shaohua.

211
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:56,860
Understood.

212
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:59,340
Okay, I'll get back to you later.

213
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:05,660
Mr. Xia came to us for help.

214
00:12:07,020 --> 00:12:07,860
Help with what?

215
00:12:09,140 --> 00:12:11,020
He said that three months ago,

216
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:12,580
through Mr. Lu's connections,

217
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:15,980
he managed to get
a batch of anti-epidemic powder

218
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:18,620
added to the procurement list
of the Zhejiang-Shanghai Allied Forces.

219
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:20,300
But less than a month later,

220
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,980
the allied forces were defeated.

221
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:23,700
Now there's no way to sell that batch.

222
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:25,580
So he's asking us for help.

223
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,100
How big is the batch?

224
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:31,860
Half a million boxes.

225
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:38,620
If we help him distribute them,

226
00:12:40,380 --> 00:12:42,300
we can sell 300 boxes a month at most.

227
00:12:42,460 --> 00:12:44,700
Even with all the branches
of Jujing Apothecary,

228
00:12:44,860 --> 00:12:46,620
selling 500,000 boxes

229
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,060
would take 20 years.

230
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:55,460
But if over 300 pharmacies in Shanghai

231
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:56,700
joined in,

232
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:58,100
they could clear the whole batch
in just six months.

233
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:01,780
The only reason they'd help

234
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:03,100
is if there's a significant profit

235
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:04,100
to be made.

236
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:07,700
The only option now
is to offload it at a loss.

237
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:11,380
Okay then, help me figure out

238
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:12,460
what kind of loss we're looking at.

239
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,580
Since it's a loss anyway,

240
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:28,020
make it a complete one.

241
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:30,700
[Jujing Apothecary]
Give them away for free?

242
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:31,620
Yes.

243
00:13:31,780 --> 00:13:34,820
There are 500,000 blue-collar workers
in Shanghai.

244
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,500
One box per person would be perfect.

245
00:13:37,340 --> 00:13:38,180
Do you have any idea

246
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:40,180
what 500,000 boxes
of anti-epidemic powder

247
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:41,140
are worth?

248
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:42,700
A hundred thousand silver dollars,

249
00:13:43,140 --> 00:13:45,140
but your cost is only 30,000.

250
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:45,860
"Only"?

251
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:49,940
That's a pretty bold claim.

252
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,140
Or there's another way.

253
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,260
Based on our numbers,

254
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:55,900
if we bring the ex-factory price

255
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:57,700
down to five wen,

256
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,100
and set the retail price at forty,

257
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,020
more than 300 pharmacies across Shanghai

258
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:03,700
would be willing to help distribute it.

259
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,180
Customers will be willing to buy,

260
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:08,780
and we can sell out

261
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:10,500
within two months.

262
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:12,300
Wouldn't that mean a loss?

263
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,860
Twenty-eight thousand silver dollars.

264
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:15,540
That's a steep hit, don't you think?

265
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:16,580
No.

266
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:17,660
Absolutely not.

267
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:21,140
We have no choice.

268
00:14:24,580 --> 00:14:25,420
I think

269
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:28,260
we should ship all this
to the north of China.

270
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:30,020
With so many customers
for Shouyuan Apothecary,

271
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:31,180
selling them shouldn't be a problem.

272
00:14:31,860 --> 00:14:32,740
This batch of anti-epidemic powder

273
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:34,620
was tailored for Zhejiang.

274
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,940
If we send it up north,

275
00:14:37,220 --> 00:14:38,300
it won't be nearly as effective.

276
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,540
That could damage our reputation.

277
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:44,220
Maybe we should put it on hold

278
00:14:44,380 --> 00:14:45,220
for now.

279
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:48,620
Let's talk about the TCM Guild election.

280
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,140
Right now,

281
00:14:50,540 --> 00:14:52,900
half the guild

282
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:56,220
thinks you're just a northerner

283
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:57,900
who came to Shanghai
to make a quick buck.

284
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:59,460
They say you are mercenary

285
00:14:59,780 --> 00:15:00,620
and cold-hearted.

286
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:03,140
So if we want to change their minds

287
00:15:03,140 --> 00:15:04,300
and turn things around

288
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,540
in a short time,

289
00:15:05,860 --> 00:15:08,500
we'll need to put in real work

290
00:15:08,940 --> 00:15:11,380
to reshape your public image.

291
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:13,820
I've done a rough estimate of the costs

292
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:15,540
for reporter interviews,

293
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:17,500
newspaper and magazine ads,

294
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:19,260
plus fliers and posters.

295
00:15:19,380 --> 00:15:19,940
Also...

296
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:21,460
Also, you need to spend more time

297
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:24,100
connecting with other members
of the TCM Guild.

298
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:27,340
Altogether, these expenses will come to

299
00:15:27,340 --> 00:15:29,980
around 32,000 silver dollars.

300
00:15:30,460 --> 00:15:31,580
This is just the bare minimum.

301
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:32,620
Yes.

302
00:15:33,020 --> 00:15:34,060
That much?

303
00:15:35,260 --> 00:15:36,700
We're already spending a fortune
on this.

304
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:39,180
Selling at a loss isn't an option,

305
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:40,380
and giving it away? No chance.

306
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:48,340
No,

307
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:50,500
we're doing it.

308
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:52,620
Let's give every last box

309
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:55,620
to the workers in Shanghai. No charge.

310
00:15:57,180 --> 00:15:58,740
Mr. Xia, should we reconsider...?

311
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:00,580
Miss Chu,

312
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:02,700
we'll leave this

313
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:03,900
in your hands.

314
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:04,580
No problem.

315
00:16:09,060 --> 00:16:12,220
[Baoxing Cotton Mill]

316
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:28,700
Excuse me,

317
00:16:28,820 --> 00:16:30,900
is today a day off?

318
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:31,580
Yes, it is.

319
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:33,460
Where did the other female workers go?

320
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:34,940
They're all over there,
listening to the speech.

321
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:35,780
Thank you.

322
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:43,180
Who built the railways?

323
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:44,980
Who drives the trains?

324
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,540
Who made the machines?

325
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:48,180
It's always been us, the workers.

326
00:16:48,940 --> 00:16:50,780
No homes without builders.

327
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:53,740
No clothes without makers.

328
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:56,020
No future without workers.

329
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:58,140
Sure, workers are great.

330
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:00,780
Then why are we still struggling?

331
00:17:00,780 --> 00:17:02,020
Because we're fated to suffer.

332
00:17:03,540 --> 00:17:05,820
No, poverty isn't fate.

333
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,300
It's because there are classes
and exploitation.

334
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,380
Why do capitalists exploit?

335
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:12,740
Because they hold power.

336
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:15,420
The workers grow poorer

337
00:17:15,420 --> 00:17:16,860
as the capitalists grow richer.

338
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:19,020
That's how this system works.

339
00:17:19,980 --> 00:17:21,260
To end poverty,

340
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:23,300
we must take power.

341
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:25,140
We need to overthrow the old regime,

342
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,860
and build a society
free of class and exploitation,

343
00:17:27,860 --> 00:17:29,500
a society where all are equal!

344
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:31,860
- Well said!
- Nice!

345
00:17:32,140 --> 00:17:33,140
- Splendid!
- Great!

346
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:35,740
Shaohua,

347
00:17:36,460 --> 00:17:38,140
do you know
what the true tide of history is?

348
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:39,260
The greatness of a nation

349
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:40,940
is to serve its country and its people.

350
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:42,820
- Splendid!
- Great!

351
00:17:46,060 --> 00:17:47,660
- Well said!
- Nice!

352
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:50,140
Shaohua?

353
00:17:51,420 --> 00:17:52,140
Shaohua.

354
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:53,700
Amei.

355
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:54,380
Shaohua,

356
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:55,740
thank you.

357
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:57,100
After I took the medicine you sent,

358
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,260
my back pain went away almost instantly.

359
00:17:58,260 --> 00:17:58,980
That's great.

360
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:00,540
I'll bring you some more next time.

361
00:18:01,060 --> 00:18:01,980
The medicine's so expensive.

362
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:03,180
I can't keep accepting it.

363
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:03,820
It's fine.

364
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:05,260
Shaohua,

365
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:07,100
I'll introduce you to someone.

366
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:08,180
Who?

367
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:10,340
Let's go.

368
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:13,380
Fight for equal rights.

369
00:18:13,380 --> 00:18:14,100
Mr. Xia.

370
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:14,860
No need.

371
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:16,780
Mr. Xia,

372
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:19,380
this is Miss Chu, whom I told you about.

373
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:24,220
Amei said

374
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,980
you're giving free medicine
to every blue-collar worker in the city?

375
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:27,940
Yes.

376
00:18:28,820 --> 00:18:30,420
But there are too many workers.

377
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:32,780
Miss Chu doesn't know where to start.

378
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:35,060
Going through the Municipal Council
won't work.

379
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,620
Factories aren't safe either.

380
00:18:36,860 --> 00:18:38,420
The foremen will skim off the top.

381
00:18:39,380 --> 00:18:40,260
Leave it to us.

382
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,900
We've got the Workers' Club,

383
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,860
League of Comrades,
and Workers' Mutual Aid Society.

384
00:18:44,060 --> 00:18:45,340
All are run by workers

385
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:46,860
and they reach every factory,

386
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:48,020
dock, and station in Shanghai.

387
00:18:48,180 --> 00:18:49,540
We'll make sure every pack of medicine

388
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:51,780
goes straight to the workers.

389
00:18:52,420 --> 00:18:53,140
Thank you.

390
00:18:54,580 --> 00:18:55,780
Actually, we owe you the thanks.

391
00:18:58,060 --> 00:18:59,060
I heard

392
00:18:59,620 --> 00:19:01,180
you've been supporting female workers

393
00:19:01,580 --> 00:19:02,780
with free checkups and medicine
these past few years.

394
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:05,180
Shaohua

395
00:19:05,460 --> 00:19:06,900
used to work here.

396
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,700
She even led us in a strike.

397
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:10,380
But back then,

398
00:19:10,740 --> 00:19:12,140
she went by a different name.

399
00:19:13,060 --> 00:19:13,660
Is that so?

400
00:19:14,380 --> 00:19:15,180
Mr. Xia,

401
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:17,540
when the workers

402
00:19:17,540 --> 00:19:19,140
distribute the anti-epidemic powder,

403
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,180
could they also hand out business cards

404
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:22,740
for Jujing Apothecary
and Wen's Pharmacy?

405
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:24,100
No problem.

406
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:25,460
Additionally,

407
00:19:25,980 --> 00:19:27,660
I suggest printing a line

408
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:28,620
on the packaging,

409
00:19:28,940 --> 00:19:30,380
encouraging workers to unite

410
00:19:30,380 --> 00:19:31,500
and fight for equal treatment.

411
00:19:31,820 --> 00:19:32,420
Okay.

412
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:33,660
Excuse me,

413
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:34,540
Mr. Xia,

414
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:35,860
I'm from Domestic
and Foreign Cotton Mill No. 8.

415
00:19:35,860 --> 00:19:37,860
We'd love to have you speak
at our place tomorrow night.

416
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:38,500
No problem.

417
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:39,580
Mr. Xia,

418
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:41,380
we are from the Printers' Union.

419
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:43,100
Are you available

420
00:19:43,340 --> 00:19:44,820
to give us a talk on Wednesday?

421
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:47,180
I'll be doing research
at Zhabei Dock during the day,

422
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:48,180
but I'm free in the evening.

423
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:49,660
Okay, see you then.

424
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:50,500
Okay.

425
00:19:50,660 --> 00:19:51,420
Mr. Xia,

426
00:19:51,860 --> 00:19:53,500
I represent the seamen from CMSNC.

427
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:55,980
We also want to join
the Shanghai General Labor Union.

428
00:19:56,260 --> 00:19:57,020
We'd love to.

429
00:19:57,180 --> 00:19:57,780
- Okay.
- Mr. Xia.

430
00:19:58,020 --> 00:19:59,380
Some workers are waiting
for you at the gate.

431
00:20:01,620 --> 00:20:02,700
For what's next,

432
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:04,140
just check in with Yin Amei.

433
00:20:04,420 --> 00:20:05,140
Excuse me.

434
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:06,060
Okay, see you.

435
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:11,260
- Shaohua.
- Shaohua.

436
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:12,180
Let's go get some water over there.

437
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:13,300
- Okay.
- Let's go.

438
00:20:14,260 --> 00:20:17,780
[Wen's Pharmacy]

439
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:29,140
Wen's Pharmacy.

440
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:31,780
Zheng.

441
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:33,860
I know.

442
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:36,340
Isn't that money due next week?

443
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:39,260
It's only Wednesday today.

444
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:42,140
Alright.

445
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:43,100
I understand.

446
00:20:43,340 --> 00:20:43,980
Okay.

447
00:20:45,140 --> 00:20:45,780
That's it.

448
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:47,380
Shaohua.

449
00:20:49,380 --> 00:20:50,340
Chu Shaohua.

450
00:20:51,580 --> 00:20:52,180
Mr. Wen,

451
00:20:52,380 --> 00:20:53,380
Ms. Chu went out.

452
00:20:54,380 --> 00:20:55,420
Um,

453
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:57,100
have the accounts
from Songjiang been prepared?

454
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:57,860
Yes.

455
00:20:57,980 --> 00:20:58,620
Give them to me.

456
00:20:58,780 --> 00:21:00,020
They've all been compiled
and given to Ms. Chu.

457
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:00,900
Where is she?

458
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,060
Sun took leave,

459
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:03,700
so Ms. Chu took over the delivery
of anti-epidemic powder.

460
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,180
Where'd she go?

461
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:06,380
Zhabei Cargo Dock.

462
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:08,180
Okay.

463
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:19,900
Thank you.

464
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:20,860
Please wait a moment.

465
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:21,900
Okay.

466
00:21:25,620 --> 00:21:27,220
Hello, sir.

467
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:29,300
May I ask where Mr. Pang is?

468
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,300
Over by the wooden house.

469
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:32,300
Okay, thank you.

470
00:21:37,140 --> 00:21:38,460
Much obliged, thanks.

471
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:51,900
If this pie

472
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,060
represents the handling fees
paid by the cargo owners,

473
00:21:55,340 --> 00:21:56,020
look,

474
00:21:57,340 --> 00:21:59,100
the dock capitalists took a big chunk,

475
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:02,220
the compradors grabbed their share,

476
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:04,660
and the foremen still took a slice.

477
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:08,020
Workers are left
with just this tiny bit.

478
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:10,220
We did all the work,

479
00:22:10,420 --> 00:22:13,180
but they walked away
with most of the money.

480
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:14,580
That's exploitation!

481
00:22:15,340 --> 00:22:16,820
If we don't want this to keep happening,

482
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:18,780
we've got to stand together
and build a union,

483
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:20,780
so we can get organized
and start a revolution.

484
00:22:22,140 --> 00:22:23,020
Get back to work!

485
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:24,340
- You can go.
- Get up!

486
00:22:24,780 --> 00:22:25,740
- Go ahead.
- Hurry up!

487
00:22:27,020 --> 00:22:27,940
A bunch of slackers!

488
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:31,060
Mr. Pang, the number you reported

489
00:22:31,060 --> 00:22:32,940
to the Dockworkers' Union

490
00:22:32,940 --> 00:22:34,100
was 416.

491
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:34,820
I've got

492
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:36,980
exactly 416 boxes
of anti-epidemic powder right here.

493
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:38,180
Check them.

494
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:39,500
If there are no problems,

495
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:41,460
[Anti-epidemic Powder]
please sign here.

496
00:22:47,820 --> 00:22:51,700
[Dispatching Room]

497
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:52,740
Why are you here?

498
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:55,940
Mr. Zheng from Songjiang says
he's got a family emergency

499
00:22:55,940 --> 00:22:56,620
and needs some money.

500
00:22:56,620 --> 00:22:58,060
He wants to settle
next month's accounts ahead of time.

501
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:59,700
Since you've got the ledger,
I came to find you.

502
00:23:00,660 --> 00:23:03,340
It's in the third drawer of my desk.

503
00:23:04,140 --> 00:23:05,060
Aren't you coming back with me?

504
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:07,180
I need to go to the Seamen's Union
to collect some documents.

505
00:23:07,460 --> 00:23:07,900
Okay.

506
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:10,780
Help! Someone fell into the water!

507
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,380
Hurry up and save him!

508
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:14,980
Anyone here know how to swim?

509
00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:16,260
Save him!

510
00:23:16,780 --> 00:23:17,780
Quick!

511
00:23:17,780 --> 00:23:19,180
Get him out!

512
00:23:19,180 --> 00:23:20,220
- Can you swim?
- Hurry!

513
00:23:21,660 --> 00:23:22,740
Is there anyone who can swim?

514
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:23,660
Hurry and go down.

515
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:28,380
Move aside!

516
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:30,140
Here, grab this!

517
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:32,540
Hold onto it!

518
00:23:37,940 --> 00:23:38,700
Quick!

519
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:39,500
Hurry!

520
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:40,260
Come back this way!

521
00:23:40,260 --> 00:23:41,580
What are you doing? Get back to work!

522
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:43,540
- What are you doing?
- What do you think you are doing?

523
00:23:43,780 --> 00:23:44,580
Get back to work!

524
00:23:44,580 --> 00:23:45,580
You don't want your wages anymore, huh?

525
00:23:45,940 --> 00:23:46,780
Move it, back to work!

526
00:23:46,980 --> 00:23:47,500
Get back to shore!

527
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,500
Get to work. Hurry up!

528
00:23:48,980 --> 00:23:49,780
- Hurry up!
- Quick!

529
00:23:49,780 --> 00:23:50,540
Xia Chu.

530
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:52,740
Get to work! I'm talking to you!

531
00:23:53,180 --> 00:23:54,780
And you lot, get back to work!

532
00:23:54,780 --> 00:23:55,620
- Get to work!
- Hurry up!

533
00:23:55,620 --> 00:23:58,020
This way!

534
00:23:58,020 --> 00:23:58,700
Hurry up!

535
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:01,380
Get to work!

536
00:24:01,580 --> 00:24:02,380
Hurry up!

537
00:24:02,380 --> 00:24:03,740
Let's pull him up.

538
00:24:05,180 --> 00:24:05,980
Here, come on.

539
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,060
Put him here.

540
00:24:07,740 --> 00:24:09,580
Let him lie on his side.

541
00:24:12,620 --> 00:24:13,260
On his side.

542
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:19,940
Come on!

543
00:24:20,380 --> 00:24:21,380
- Pull him up!
- Give him a hand!

544
00:24:21,820 --> 00:24:22,420
Pitch in.

545
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:23,940
Pull! Quick!

546
00:24:24,780 --> 00:24:25,220
Come on!

547
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:31,340
Move aside.

548
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:41,380
Wake up.

549
00:24:46,820 --> 00:24:48,100
Come on.

550
00:24:59,300 --> 00:24:59,860
Wake up.

551
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:01,420
Wake up!

552
00:25:04,820 --> 00:25:05,580
Help me

553
00:25:05,820 --> 00:25:06,500
get him up.

554
00:25:07,620 --> 00:25:08,700
- Buddy!
- He's awake.

555
00:25:09,220 --> 00:25:10,980
Buddy.

556
00:25:12,540 --> 00:25:13,780
Thank you, Mr. Xia.

557
00:25:13,940 --> 00:25:15,660
We'll never forget this, Mr. Xia.

558
00:25:15,660 --> 00:25:16,100
No need for that.

559
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:17,180
- It's no big deal.
- Thanks a lot, Mr. Xia.

560
00:25:17,180 --> 00:25:17,900
Please get up.

561
00:25:18,180 --> 00:25:19,060
We owe you, Mr. Xia.

562
00:25:19,060 --> 00:25:20,020
Please get up.

563
00:25:20,020 --> 00:25:20,740
You call the shots

564
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:21,860
on union matters.

565
00:25:22,020 --> 00:25:23,020
We'll do whatever you say.

566
00:25:23,220 --> 00:25:25,140
- Right!
